  "instructions": [
    "1. Preheat grill to medium-high heat.",
    "2. In a large bowl, whisk together smoked paprika, roasted garlic powder, olive oil, lemon juice, salt, and black pepper.",
    "3. Add the chicken to the bowl and marinate for at least 30 minutes, or up to 2 hours in the refrigerator.",
    "4. Thread the marinated chicken, sliced red bell pepper, and onion onto skewers.",
    "5. Grill the skewers for 8-10 minutes, turning occasionally, until the chicken is cooked through and slightly charred.",
    "6. Garnish with chopped parsley and serve immediately."
